Ask HN: Biographies of Companies or Things?
text:
I've enjoyed books narrating the history of a company or a thing, like David McCullough's The Path Between the Seas, Jon Gertner's The Idea Factory or Dava Sobel's Longitude.

But, missing a name for this particular genre, I have a hard time finding new entries. Does HN have anything of that kind to recommend?

Ask HN: Coffee Shops to Work from in NYC
text:
What is your favorite coffee shop to work out of in New York City?

Here are a few of mine

- Ground Central Coffee Company (888 8th Ave and 155 East 52nd Street) 7am to 7pm - Think Coffee (248 Mercer St and 1 Bleecker St) 7am to 7pm (one is open until 10pm) - Kaffe Landskap NYC (South) 275 Greenwich St

I look for places with seating, wifi, power and good hours of operation.
